            <div facs="ht:chi.12945678&amp;view=1up&amp;seq=628" type="entry">
                <p><label type="entry">VELVET</label>, a rich kind of stuff, all silk, covered on
                    the outside with a close, short, fine, soft shag, the other side being a very
                    strong close tissue. The nap or shag, called also the <hi rend="italic"
                        >velveting,</hi> of this stuff, is formed of part of the threads of the
                    warp, which the workman puts on a long narrow-channelled ruler or needle, which
                    he afterwards cuts, by drawing a sharp steel tool along the channel of the
                    needle to the ends of the warp.</p>
            </div>
